data.content:
## .NET 10 OpenAPI Breaking Changes

The root cause is **Microsoft.OpenApi upgraded from v1 to v2**, which adopted OpenAPI 3.1 and replaced custom types with `System.Text.Json.Nodes`.

Here are the **4 breaks** in your code and their fixes:

### 1. `OpenApiString` removed (`Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace gone)
All `IOpenApiAny` types replaced with `JsonNode`:
```csharp
// Old
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// New
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` no longer extends `Dictionary`
It now has a `Schemes` property:
```csharp
// Old
new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }

// New
new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
{
    Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
    {
        [oAuthScheme] = scopes
    }
}
```

### 3. `schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 expresses nullability via the `type` array. Use the `JsonSchemaType` flags enum:
```csharp
// Old
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// New — to explicitly remove null from the type union:
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```
(Add `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;` — `JsonSchemaType` lives there.)

### 4. `ReferenceType` enum renamed
```csharp
// Old
Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }

// New
Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
```
This one actually stayed the same — no change needed.

---

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new()
        {
            Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecurityScheme, IList<string>>
            {
                [oAuthScheme] = scopes
            }
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary:** Remove the `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` using, add `System.Text.Json.Nodes`, replace `OpenApiString` → `JsonValue.Create()`, restructure `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` to use `.Schemes`, and replace `.Nullable = false` with the `JsonSchemaType` flag manipulation.
